{
  "texts": [
    "The quality assurance methods used in the food industry have traditionally involved human visual inspection.",
    "Such methods are tedious, laborious, time-consuming, and inconsistent.",
    "Thus, HSI with all its advantages for non-invasive and non-destructive quality evaluation ability, emerges as the solution to the limitations in the agri-food sector.",
    "However, the higher cost and increased complexities hinder the widespread applicability of HSI technology.",
    "Therefore, reconstructing HSI from commonly available RGB images could be a more affordable solution, expanding its applications in the agriculture and food sectors."
  ]
}